9|AI Consulting — Licensing Models — Completed Jul 19, 2026. Key findings: (1) "No Training on Client Data" is the #1 highest-frequency redline from enterprise AI buyers in 2025-2026 (per WCR Legal, Finberg Firm, Jacobs Counsel); (2) Absence of this clause triggers a presumption that training use is permitted, which is commercially untenable for regulated clients; (3) MSA v1.6 was missing this covenant — added §3.9 (Client Data — No Training or Model Improvement) with six sub-sections: definition, no training use, no incorporation, permitted uses, deletion obligation, flow-down obligation; (4) Updated Clause Genome §14 (Six-Artefact Framework — cross-reference to MSA §3.9), §8 (Data/DPA — training prohibition), §23 (API ToS Conflict — MSA implementation reference). Updated Genome 1.13.0→1.14.0, MSA 1.6→1.7. Also flagged EU PLD reform (Dec 9, 2026) as a 2026 regulatory development treating AI software as "products" under strict liability — relevant for EU-facing engagements.
